OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FOfcom: Lord Michael Grade  
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fconfirmed as chairman      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, TV executive and businessman Lord Grade
OL,6, has been confirmed as the new chairman 
OL,7, of UK media regulator Ofcom.           
OL,9,FThe former BBC chairman, who has been a
OL,10,FConservative peer since 2011, has been 
OL,11,Fappointed by Culture Secretary Nadine  
OL,12,FDorries for four years from 1 May 2022 
OL,13,Fto 30 April 2026.                      
OL,15,FThe Department for Culture, Media and  
OL,16,FSport says he will earn #142,500 annual
OL,17,Fsalary for working three days per week.
OL,19,FLord Grade said last week he was       
OL,20,F"privileged" to be asked.              
